3. ffprobe -v error -show_format -of json talk_audio.mp3 (verify)
4. Report the output path, duration, and the exact command.

## Error recovery (error text -> exact next command)
"No such file or directory" -> ls -la the directory the input should be in, copy the exact filename from the listing, retry once
"Invalid argument" / usage error -> ffmpeg -hide_banner -h filter=NAME (for filter syntax) or ffmpeg -hide_banner -h encoder=NAME, copy the exact option names, retry once
"Unknown encoder" / encoder not found -> ffmpeg -hide_banner -encoders | grep -i NAME, pick a real encoder from the list, retry once
"already exists" (output) -> choose a new output name with a numeric suffix (OUTPUT_trim_2.mp4), retry once; never add -y
"Output file does not contain any stream" -> re-probe the input and check stream mapping; add explicit -map 0:v and -map 0:a
moov atom not found / Invalid data found -> the input is corrupt or truncated; report the blocker, do not attempt repair unless asked

## Command rules
Use ffmpeg and ffprobe for media work.
NEVER overwrite the input file. Always write a NEW output file with a descriptive suffix. Always pass -n (never -y).
Verify every output with ffprobe (or ls -la for images/gifs) before reporting.
Prefer -c copy whenever the task does not require re-encoding.
Do not browse the web, generate images, use external search tools, or edit files unless the user explicitly asks.
Do not use apply_patch unless the user explicitly asks to modify files.

